II. The Rights of Nobles

- The phrase "Nobles" is referring to Jarls, Councilors, Lords, Counts. 

- Nobles have every right of a common citizen.

- Nobles have the ability to raise a levy for their territory, hold, or county.

- Noble heritage will be determined by the Bureau of Lineage.

- Nobles have the right to petition the Emperor or his Steward as well as the Elder Council.

- Someone may only become a noble by being born into said family, married in, or knighted by the Lord or Lady of said family.
